ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: BEGINGRAPH </ option(s)> ; 
      <GTL-global-statements >
      GTL-layout-block
      <GTL-global-statements >
    ENDGRAPH ; 

Defines the outermost container for a single GTL-layout-block and one or more GTL-global-statements.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: LAYOUT DATALATTICE argument(s) </ option(s)> ;
    graph-prototype-block ;
    <sidebar-statement-block(s);>
  ENDLAYOUT ; 

Creates a grid of graphs based on one or two classification variables and a graphical prototype.

[Syntax: LAYOUT PROTOTYPE </option(s)>; 
    plot-statements;

    <INNERMARGIN </options(s)>; 
      block-plot-statement(s); | axis-table statement(s);
    ENDINNERMARGIN;> 

    <... more-innermargin-blocks ...> > 
  ENDLAYOUT; 

Builds a composite from one or more plot-statements. The composite is used as a prototype or "rubber stamp" 
that repeats in each cell of a parent DATALATTICE or DATAPANEL layout.

Syntax: LAYOUT DATAPANEL CLASSVARS= (class-var1 ... class-varN) </ option(s)> ; 
  graph-prototype-block ;
  <sidebar-statement-block(s);>
  ENDLAYOUT ; 

Creates a grid of graphs based on one or more classification variables and a graphical prototype. 
By default, a separate instance of the prototype (a data cell) is created for each actual combination 
of the classification variables.

Syntax: LAYOUT GRIDDED </ option(s)> ; 
  GTL-statements ;
  ENDLAYOUT ; 

Assembles the results of nested GTL-statements into a grid.

Syntax: LAYOUT GLOBALLEGEND </option(s)>; 
    <discreteLegend-statement(s) | mergedLegend-statement(s)>; 
  ENDLAYOUT; 

Creates a compound legend containing multiple discrete legends positioned at the bottom of a graph. 

Restrictions: Only one global legend is allowed in a graph. 

The LAYOUT GLOBALLEGEND statement must be placed directly inside the BEGINGRAPH block. It is not valid outside 
of the BEGINGRAPH block. Continuous legends are not supported inside the global legend.  

When the LAYOUT GLOBALLEGEND block is used, all of the template's legend statements must be specified within 
the LAYOUT GLOBALLEGEND block. Any legend statements that are specified outside of the LAYOUT GLOBALLEGEND 
block are ignored.

Syntax: LAYOUT LATTICE </ option(s)> ; 
  GTL-statement(s) | cell-statement-block(s);
  <axis-statement-block(s);>
  <header-statement-block(s);>
  <sidebar-statement-block(s);>
  ENDLAYOUT ; 

Creates a grid of graphs that automatically aligns plot areas and tick display areas across grid cells 
to facilitate data comparisons among graphs.

Syntax: LAYOUT OVERLAY </ option(s)> ; 
  GTL-statements ;
  ENDLAYOUT ; 

Builds a composite from one or more GTL-statements. The composite could be an entire graph, or if 
this layout is nested in a GRIDDED or LATTICE layout, the composite typically provides contents for 
one cell in the parent layout.

Syntax: LAYOUT OVERLAYEQUATED </ option(s)> ; 
  GTL-statements ;
  ENDLAYOUT ; 

Builds a composite from one or more GTL-statements. The composite could be an entire graph, or if 
this layout is nested in another layout, such as a GRIDDED layout, the composite typically provides 
contents for one cell in the parent layout. an OVERLAYEQUATED layout, the display unit of the X axis 
always equals the display unit of the Y axis.

Syntax: LAYOUT OVERLAY3D </ option(s)> ; 
  GTL-statements ;
  ENDLAYOUT ; 

Builds a 3D composite from one or more GTL-statements. The composite could be an entire graph, 
or if this layout is nested in a GRIDDED or LATTICE layout, the composite typically provides 
contents for one cell in the parent layout.

Syntax: LAYOUT REGION </option(s)>; 
    GTL-statements;
  ENDLAYOUT;

Creates the drawing area for a plot that does not use axes.

Syntax: BARCHART X= column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

The following syntax creates a bar chart with bars representing summarized values of Y categorized by X:

  BARCHART X= column | expression Y= numeric-column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Creates a barchart computed from input data.

Syntax: BARCHARTPARM X= column | expression
      Y= numeric-column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Creates a barchart specified by pre-summarized data.

Syntax: BOXPLOT Y= numeric-column | expression < / option(s)> ; 

BOXPLOT X= column | expression
      Y= numeric-column | expression < / option(s)> ; 

Creates box-and-whisker plot(s) computed from input data.

Syntax: BOXPLOTPARM Y= numeric-column | expression
      STAT= string-column </ option(s)> ; 

BOXPLOTPARM X= column | expression
      Y= numeric-column | expression
      STAT= string-column </ option(s)> ; 

Creates side-by-side box-and-whisker plots specified by parameters.

Syntax: DROPLINE X= x-axis-value | column | expression
      Y= y-axis-value | column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Creates a horizontal or vertical drop line from a point to an axis.

Syntax: ELLIPSE X= numeric-column | expression
      Y= numeric-column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Creates a confidence ellipse computed from input data.

Syntax: HISTOGRAMPARM X = numeric-column | expression
      Y = non-negative-numeric-column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Creates a univariate histogram for specified values of bin midpoints and bin frequencies.

Syntax: LINECHART CATEGORY=column | expression </option(s)> ; 

LINECHART CATEGORY=column | expression 
RESPONSE=numeric-column | expression </option(s) > ; 

Creates a line chart that is computed from input data.

Syntax: LOESSPLOT X = numeric-column | expression
      Y = numeric-column | expression </ <regression-options> <option(s)>> ; 

Creates a fitted loess curve computed from input data.

Syntax: NEEDLEPLOT X = column | expression
      Y = numeric-column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Creates a plot of observations as points connected to a baseline by vertical line segments.

Syntax: PBSPLINEPLOT X = numeric-column | expression
      Y = numeric-column | expression </ <regression-options> <option(s)>> ; 

Creates a fitted penalized B-spline curve computed from input data.

Syntax: REFERENCELINE X= x-axis-value | column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Syntax for creating a line perpendicular to the Y-axis at a Y-intercept:

  REFERENCELINE Y= y-axis-value | column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Creates a horizontal or vertical reference line.

Syntax: REGRESSIONPLOT X = numeric-column | expression
      Y = numeric-column | expression </ <regression-options> <option(s)>> ; 

Creates a fitted regression line or curve computed from input data.

Syntax: SCATTERPLOT X= column | expression
      Y= column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Creates a scatter plot of input data.

Syntax: SERIESPLOT X= column | expression
      Y= column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Displays a series of line segments that connect observations of input data.

Syntax: STEPPLOT X= column | expression
      Y= numeric-column | expression </ option(s)> ; 

Displays a series of horizontal and vertical line segments that connect observations of input data.

Syntax: PIECHART CATEGORY=column | discrete-attr-var | expression  </option(s)>; 

PIECHART CATEGORY=column | discrete-attr-var | expression
RESPONSE=numeric-column | expression </option(s)>; 

Creates a pie chart that is computed from input data.

Syntax: ENDGRAPH;

Marks the end of the outermost container for a single GTL-layout-block and one or more 
GTL-global-statements.

Syntax: DISCRETEATTRMAP NAME="string" </option(s)>; 
    VALUE value-spec </option(s)>; 
    <... more VALUE statements ...>
  ENDDISCRETEATTRMAP;

Defines a set of graphical properties that can be associated with user-defined sets of values.

Syntax: VALUE value-spec </option(s)>; 

A VALUE statement within the DISCRETEATTRMAP block associates graphical properties with a discrete 
value in the attribute map.

Syntax: COLUMNAXES ;  
    AXISCOMP axis-option(s);  
  ENDCOLUMNAXES;  

Specifies the primary (bottom) axes for the columns:

Requirement: You must specify an ENDCOLUMNAXES statement to complete the COLUMNAXES 
statement block.

Syntax: COLUMN2AXES ;  
    AXISCOMP axis-option(s);  
  ENDCOLUMN2AXES; 

Specifies the secondary (top) axes for the columns.

Requirement: You must specify an ENDCOLUMN2AXES statement to complete the COLUMN2AXES 
statement block.

Syntax: ROWAXES ;  
    AXISCOMP axis-option(s); 
  ENDROWAXES;  

Specifies the primary (left) axes for the rows.

Requirement: You must specify an ENDROWAXES statement to complete the ROWAXES statement block.

Syntax: ROW2AXES ;  
    AXISCOMP axis-option(s); 
  ENDROW2AXES;  

Specifies the secondary (right) axes for the rows.

Requirement: You must specify an ENDROW2AXES statement to complete the ROW2AXES statement block.

Syntax: ROWHEADERS ; 

Specifies a header for the primary (left) row-header position. ENTRY statements 
can be used to specify rotated text.

Syntax: ROW2HEADERS ; 

Specifies a header for the secondary (right) row-header position. ENTRY statements 
can be used to specify rotated text.

Syntax: CELL;  <CELLHEADER; 
    ODS-Graph-statement(s); 
    ENDCELLHEADER;>  

    ODS-Graph-statement(s);  
    ENDCELL;   

Signals the beginning of a CELL block; 

Requirement: You must specify an ENDCELL statement to complete the CELL statement block. 

Tip: If a CELLHEADER statement block is not specified inside of a CELL statement block, then 
the enclosed ODS-Graph-statement(s) produces the same results as if the ODS-Graph-statement(s) 
were specified outside of the CELL statement block.

Syntax: SIDEBAR </ ALIGN=TOP|BOTTOM|RIGHT|LEFT> ; 

Signals the beginning of a SIDEBAR block; 

Four sidebar areas are available: two that span all columns (one on the TOP and one 
on the BOTTOM), and two that span all rows (one on the RIGHT and one on the LEFT).

Syntax: INNERMARGIN < /option(s)>; 
      block-plot-statement(s); | axis-table statement(s);

    ENDINNERMARGIN;

Provides a nested region in a LAYOUT OVERLAY or LAYOUT PROTOTYPE container in which a block plot 
or axis table can be placed.

GTL supports conditional logic that enables you to include or exclude one or more 
GTL statements at runtime: 

Syntax: 
IF ( condition ) 
  GTL statement(s); 
ELSE
  GTL statement(s); 
ENDIF ;

